Class08Notes

Implicit wait:
Will be applied for findElement method
it waits until locate the element    **yani sadece element locate ederken lazım olur

Explicit wait for WebDriver Wait:
is used to tell the webdriver to wait for a certain condition before **bu aşırı kapsamlı bir waittir class11rightclik örneğine bak
throwing an exception for a specified condition

Explicit wait work with ExpectedConditions class and waits until certain conditions are
met or the given time is achieved

Fluent Wait --> global wait
it used to tell webdriver to certain condition as well as its frequency
before throwing an exception

Implicit wait -- waits to locate the element
Explicit wait -- wait until certain condition
Fluent wait -- sets timeouts, polling and ignores needed exceptions

WebTables
WebTables are elements on the webPage , which are constructed by having rows and columns

Types of WebTables:
1. Static webtable
2. Dynamic webtable

WebTabels consist of different sections or parts:
<table>
    <thead>
            <tr>
                <th> </th> -- column data or heading
            <tr>
    <thead>
    <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td> </td> -- table data
                <tr>
    <tbody>
<table>
